0050|- [HelpText]
0051|STechnical structure of SURVO MM
S   | 8888888888888888888888888888888
0053|*SURVO MM is written in the C language using WIN32 API library functions.
0054|SIt works in Windows 95, 98, NT, 2000, Me, and XP, 7 and 8 environments.
S   |                     2222222222222222222222222
0055|*SURVO MM consists of a family of program modules. The main module
0056|*is the SURVO MM editor which calls other modules as child processes
0057|*when needed (according to the user's actions). The user has no need to
0058|*know the internal structure of the system.
0060|*SURVO MM has been created directly by using the source code of the
0061|*earlier version SURVO 98 as the basis. In typical statistical modules,
0062|*for examples, only slight changes are needed. On the contrary,
0063|*all routines handling the keyboard, screen and mouse have been rewritten
0064|*using WIN32 functions.
0066|*The current number of SURVO MM modules (EXE files) is about 100.
0067|*Typically one module contains the program code of several SURVO MM commands
0068|*and operations. Furtheremore there are about 700 other system
0069|*files like sucros (Survo macros), files of the help system, drivers, etc.
S   |                                                                      1
