0086|- [HelpText]
0087|*SURVO MM allows creating and saving of edit fields up to the capacity
0088|*of the central memory of the computer. For example, in a 128KB memory
0089|*it is possible to maintain edit fields of 500000 lines with 100 or
0090|Smore columns. The maximum number of columns is 996 (10006 from ver.3)
S   |                                                222
0091|*but there is no (practical) upper limit for the number of lines.
0092|*Very large fields are needed only in special applications and temporary
0093|*situations; for example, when irregular text files (created elsewhere)
0094|*should be polished. In general, it is not wise to keep big data sets in
0095|*the edit field.
0097|*When an edit field does not exceed the capacity of SURVO 84C (about
0098|*60000 bytes), it is saved in SURVO MM (by the SAVE command) exactly
0099|*in the same way as in SURVO 84C.
0100|*Large fields with more than 252 columns and/or too many lines are
0101|*saved in a new form where only non-empty lines (with their line
0102|*numbers and possible shadow lines) are stored. Also trailing blanks
0103|*are omitted and thus much space is spared on the disk.
0104|*These SURVO MM edit files are in fact simple text files.
0105|*`Over-sized' edit files cannot be used in SURVO 84C as edit fields
0106|*but they can be treated there as text files (by LOADP and SHOW).
0108|SAn over-sized edit field is indicated by a red square   almost at the end
S   |                                                       P
0109|*of the header line.
0111|*As an option (in dealing with certain system files) an over-sized
0112|*edit field can be saved in the old SURVO 84C format by setting
0113|*string "(84ED)" in the comment of the SAVE command on the first edit line.
0114|*Example:
0116|*    1 *SAVE BIGTEXT / over-sized field (84ED)
0117|*    2 *
0118|* -----
0119|* 9999 *
0120|*10000 * This is the last line!
0122|*This (84ED) option should be never used in standard applications
0123|*since it creates very large files.
