0132|- [HelpText]
0133|*Data files have the same structure as in SURVO 84C and 98.
0134|*Thus all data files (with the .SVO extension) created in SURVO 84C
0135|*are accepted in SURVO MM.
0136|*However, there is one important extension in SURVO MM: In data files
0137|*with very many fields (variables) SURVO MM permits long explanations
0138|*in names of fields. In SURVO 84C the total amount of text in these
0139|*names and other descriptions of fields is limited to 65500 bytes.
0141|*In SURVO 84C the maximum number of elements in a matrix was 8100, i.e.
0142|*90x90 is the largest allowed size for a square matrix. In SURVO MM
0143|*it is possible to operate with much larger matrices. For example,
0144|*In a 128MB memory one may handle 1000x1000 matrices by various MAT operations.
0145|*Again representations are identical in both systems.
