0170|*Sucros made in SURVO 84C and 98 work similarly in SURVO MM.
0171|*In fact, the regular collections of sucros located in the S and TUT
0172|*When a sucro is activated in SURVO MM, it is searched for in this order:
0174|*  1. Current data directory of SURVO MM (for example, D:\DEMO1)
0175|*  2. `sucropath' defined in SURVO.APU of SURVO MM
0176|*  3. <Survo>\U\S   (<Survo> is the main directory of SURVO MM.)
S   |      <     >        <     >
0177|*  4. <Survo>\U\TUT (This directory is not needed anymore.)
S   |      <     >
0178|*  5. <Survo>\S
S   |      <     >
0179|*  6. <Survo>\TUT
S   |      <     >
0181|*By the sucro command
0182|*/WHICH <name_of_sucro>
S   |        <             >
0183|*the current instance of a sucro is automatically detected.
