0193|- [HelpText]
0194|*Using the clipboard in SURVO MM
0196|*Survo has always had a 'clipboard' of its own. It is controlled by
0197|- shadow %: [LINK(q02_17.html)] [/LINK]
0198|Sthe BLOCK (alt-F4) key (See BLOCK?) or by the mouse (See MOUSE6?).
S   |                             %%%%%   888888888888888888888888888888
0200|*In SURVO MM (in versions 1.15+) a text block painted by the BLOCK key
0201|*can also be copied to the Windows Clipboard directly by clicking
0202|*the soft button c (copy).
0203|*The text in the clipboard is thereafter available for any other
0204|*Windows program.
0205|*Correspondingly, any text appearing in in the Windows Clipboard
0206|*can be pasted in the edit field to the place indicated by the cursor
0207|*by double-clicking the soft button p (paste) or by the command PASTE.
0208|*If the insert mode (set by the INS key) is on, the text in the clip-
0209|*board will be inserted between the current edit lines. If the insert
0210|*mode is off, the clipboard text will be written over the possible
0211|*current text.
0212|*From version 2.37 the Windows clipboard can be maintained by keys
0213|*ctrl+ins (COPY), shift+ins (PASTE).
0214|*See also the COPY command (COPY2?)
0215|*More information on next pages:
0217|*Copying a text block to the Survo and Windows clipboards:
0218|*1. Press the BLOCK key (alt-F4).
0219|*2. Move (by the mouse or arrow keys) the cursor to the upper-left
0220|*   corner of the text block to be copied
0221|*   and press BLOCK again.
0222|*3. Move the cursor to the lower-right corner of the text block and
0223|*   press BLOCK still once. The block then appears in a painted form.
0224|*4. Click by the mouse the soft button c which copies the text into
0225|S   the clipboard or press ctrl+ins. A temporary message of the form
S   |                  88888888888888888
0226|*      The text block is now copied to the clipboard!
0227|*   confirms this fact and painting of the block disappears.
0229|*Thereafter the text block now copied to the Windows Clipboard
0230|*is available also in other Windows programs in a normal way.
0232|*Note 1: The text in the clipboard does not contain shadow lines.
0233|*Note 2: However, at the same time the entire text block with shadows
0234|*        will be saved in the own clipboard of Survo and it can be
0235|*        copied later to any edit field directly by pressing
0236|*        the BLOCK key four times.
0238|*Pasting text from the Windows Clipboard to the edit field:
0239|*1. Move (by the mouse or the arrow keys) the cursor to the position
0240|*   wherefrom the text should start.
0241|*2. If you want that the text from the clipboard will not overwrite
0242|*   existing text, enter the insert mode by the INS key.
0243|*3. Paste the contents of the Windows Clipboard by the soft button p
0244|S   (double-click!) or press shift+ins.
S   |                    888888888888888888
0246|- [New]
0247|*Text from the clipboard can also be pasted by the following command
0248|*LOADW CLIPBOARD / SPLIT=SP
0249|*or by the key sucro P (by pressing three keys: F2 M P).
