0259|- [HelpText]
0260|*Several SURVO MM sessions may be running simultaneously.
0261|*Each session is initiated by clicking the SURVO MM icon.
0262|*Thus the user may type a research report in one session while another
0263|*copy of Survo is carrying out a long simulation experiment.
0265|*If you want to use this multisession property very heavily (many
0266|*Survos doing hard work automatically at the same time) it is good to set
0267|*session_tmp=1
0268|*in the SURVO.APU file.
0270|*By this setting each Survo session will have its own subdirectory for
0271|*temporary files and then there will be no confusion with those files
0272|*although concurrent Survo sessions are performing similar tasks.
0274|*For a temporary usage a "slave Survo" can be called by keys F2 M Z.
0275|*More information by activating
0276|*/Z ?
0278|*Temporary files:
0279|*Many Survo program modules are creating and using various temporary
0280|*files for saving intermediate results, for example.
0282|*Temporary files are saved in the directory
0283|*<Survo>\TMP (typically C:\Program Files\SURVO\TMP) or according to
S   | <     >
0284|*etmpd=<path>
S   |       <    >
0285|*given in the SURVO.APU file.
0287|*To provide a separate subdirectory for temporary files in each Survo
0288|*session,
0289|*session_tmp=1
0290|*must be given in SURVO.APU.
0291|*Then these subdirectories are created by Survo and they are
0292|*<Survo>\TMP\A, <Survo>\TMP\B, etc. by default.
S   | <     >        <     >
0293|*In this case the corresponding subdirectory is also removed when the
0294|*Survo session is terminated. However, if del_tmp=0 is given in
0295|*SURVO.APU, the subdirectory for temporary files is not removed.
